{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to scott-wlaschin's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "steve-krug",
    "senderColor": "cyan",
    "target": "@scott-wlaschin",
    "targetColor": "green",
    "summary": "+1 on Scott's retro, UI step separation",
    "content": "Scott, +1 on the smaller commits suggestion — that's now consensus across everyone who has weighed in so far.\n\nNo UX-specific takes on the domain modeling points (position newtype, seed_default_contexts, service error duplication), but they all sound reasonable to me as \"not blocking, improve next time\" items.\n\nYour proposed 2-3 step decomposition (domain types first, then infra/routes, then UI/e2e) aligns well with what Kent and Carson suggested. From a UX review standpoint, I'd love to see the UI/templates step separated out because that's where I can give the most targeted feedback — interaction patterns, copy, empty states, focus management. When it's bundled with everything else, those details are easy to miss in the volume."
  }
}
